The report on the DE-CIX website shows another indication that Germany might at least be involved in the US electoral fraud. DE-CIX writes that on November 4, 2020 the DE-CIX (German Commercial Internet Exchange) in Frankfurt set a new record in data throughput. At 10 terabits per second, a new sound barrier was broken on November 3rd - i.e. on the day of the US election - shortly after 8 p.m. (2 p.m. Washington time). The data throughput at the Frankfurt Internet node has even increased by 40 percent. An annual increase of around 10 percent is normal.

Who caused the high data throughput and where did the data go?

The Europeans are now worried their own elections have been altered.
